{"type":"text","timestamp":1775882441677,"sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad713040017RjVO7yuxgrvzR","messageID":"msg_d7ad6e749001Ou40sXr9vueWqX","sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis, the RBAC templates already exist. I'll now create comprehensive tests for the RBAC configuration as specified in the design document.","time":{"start":1775882441675,"end":1775882441675}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882442107,"sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad793cd001VaJ0K7RE8x0UjF","messageID":"msg_d7ad6e749001Ou40sXr9vueWqX","sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-10be15e43cac491f881facb7a9a87b9b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"suite: Test RBAC Configuration\ntemplates:\n  - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n  - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n  - templates/router/rbac.yaml\ntests:\n  - it: Creates all RBAC resources when enabled\n    set:\n      controllerManager.enabled: true\n      workloadManager.enabled: true\n      router.enabled: true\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n      workloadManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n      router.serviceAccount.create: true\n      controllerManager.rbac.create: true\n      workloadManager.rbac.create: true\n      router.rbac.create: true\n    asserts:\n      - isKind:\n          of: ServiceAccount\n      - isKind:\n          of: Role\n      - isKind:\n          of: RoleBinding\n      - isKind:\n          of: ClusterRole\n      - isKind:\n          of: ClusterRoleBinding\n\n  - it: Skips RBAC creation when disabled\n    set:\n      controllerManager.rbac.create: false\n      workloadManager.rbac.create: false\n      router.rbac.create: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Uses existing ServiceAccount when create is false\n    set:\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: false\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.name: existing-sa\n      workloadManager.serviceAccount.create: false\n      workloadManager.serviceAccount.name: existing-wm-sa\n      router.serviceAccount.create: false\n      router.serviceAccount.name: existing-router-sa\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Applies custom RBAC rules for controller-manager\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    set:\n      controllerManager.rbac.rules:\n        - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n          resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n          verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].resources\n          value: [\"configmaps\"]\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].verbs\n          value: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n\n  - it: Controller-manager Role has empty rules by default\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: rules\n          value: []\n\n  - it: Router Role has only secrets permission\n    templates:\n      - templates/router/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].resources\n          value: [\"secrets\"]\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].verbs\n          value: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].apiGroups\n          value: [\"\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD permissions\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n            resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n            verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD status permissions\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n            resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n            verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has core resource permissions\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"\"]\n            resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n            verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has pod status permissions\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"\"]\n            resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n            verbs: [\"get\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has event permissions\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"\"]\n            resources: [\"events\"]\n            verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n\n  - it: ServiceAccounts have correct labels\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.app.kubernetes.io/component\n          value: controller-manager\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.helm.sh/chart\n          value: agentcube-1.0.0\n\n  - it: Role has correct labels\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 0\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.app.kubernetes.io/component\n          value: controller-manager\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.helm.sh/chart\n          value: agentcube-1.0.0\n\n  - it: ClusterRole has correct labels\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 0\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.app.kubernetes.io/component\n          value: workload-manager\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.labels.helm.sh/chart\n          value: agentcube-1.0.0\n\n  - it: ServiceAccount names follow convention\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: agentcube\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: agentcube-workload-manager\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: agentcube-router\n\n  - it: RoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 1\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].kind\n          value: ServiceAccount\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].name\n          value: agentcube\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.kind\n          value: Role\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.name\n          value: agentcube\n\n  - it: ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 1\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].kind\n          value: ServiceAccount\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].name\n          value: agentcube-workload-manager\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.kind\n          value: ClusterRole\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.name\n          value: agentcube-workload-manager\n\n  - it: ServiceAccount annotations are applied\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n    set:\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations:\n        eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n        custom.annotation: custom-value\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.annotations.eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn\n          value: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.annotations.custom.annotation\n          value: custom-value\n\n  - it: Custom ServiceAccount name is used when specified\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n    set:\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.name: custom-sa-name\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: custom-sa-name\n\n  - it: Router RoleBinding references correct Role\n    templates:\n      - templates/router/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 1\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.kind\n          value: Role\n      - equal:\n          path: roleRef.name\n          value: agentcube-router\n\n  - it: Controller-manager disabled skips all RBAC resources\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    set:\n      controllerManager.enabled: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Workload manager disabled skips all RBAC resources\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    set:\n      workloadManager.enabled: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Router disabled skips all RBAC resources\n    templates:\n      - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/router/rbac.yaml\n    set:\n      router.enabled: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: RoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 1\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].namespace\n          value: agentcube\n\n  - it: ClusterRoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n    templates:\n      - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n    documentIndex: 1\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: subjects[0].namespace\n          value: agentcube\n\n  - it: All RBAC resources use correct namespace\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n      - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n      - templates/router/rbac.yaml\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.namespace\n          value: agentcube\n\n  - it: Custom namespace is used when specified\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n    set:\n      global.namespaceOverride: custom-namespace\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.namespace\n          value: custom-namespace\n\n  - it: fullnameOverride is used in resource names\n    templates:\n      - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n    set:\n      fullnameOverride: custom-fullname\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: metadata.name\n          value: custom-fullname","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/rbac_test.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:11] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [2:13] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"v1\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"kind\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [3:7] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"ServiceAccount\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"metadata\"\nERROR [4:9] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [5:3] Unexpected scalar token in YA