{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882520209,"sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad8c662001eFKxTFbfklJinT","messageID":"msg_d7ad855e8001m4kpMRjFYTbtrd","sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-eebf15512499442197e37e16916f6ba4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# RBAC Tests for AgentCube Helm Chart\n\nThis directory contains comprehensive tests for the RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration of the AgentCube Helm chart.\n\n## Test Structure\n\n```\ntests/\n├── rbac_test.yaml                          # Helm unit tests for RBAC templates\n├── controller-manager_test.yaml           # Controller manager tests\n├── router_test.yaml                        # Router tests\n├── workload-manager_test.yaml             # Workload manager tests\n└── integration/                            # Integration and security tests\n    ├── test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_router_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_controller_manager_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n    ├── test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n    ├── test_least_privilege.sh\n    ├── test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\n    └── test_token_automount.sh\n```\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Helm** (v3.x)\n- **kubectl** configured with cluster access\n- **Helm unittest plugin** for unit tests\n- Access to a Kubernetes cluster (for integration tests)\n\n### Installing Helm unittest plugin\n\n```bash\nhelm plugin install https://github.com/quintush/helm-unittest\n```\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Unit Tests (Helm Template Tests)\n\nRun all unit tests:\n\n```bash\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n```\n\nRun specific test file:\n\n```bash\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -f tests/rbac_test.yaml\n```\n\nRun tests with verbose output:\n\n```bash\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -v\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nIntegration tests require a deployed AgentCube instance. Run them from the project root:\n\n```bash\n# Test workload manager permissions\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh [namespace]\n\n# Test router permissions\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh [namespace]\n\n# Test controller manager permissions (should NOT have delete permissions)\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh [namespace]\n\n# Deploy with custom RBAC\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n\n# Deploy with existing ServiceAccount\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n```\n\n### Security Tests\n\nRun security tests to verify RBAC best practices:\n\n```bash\n# Test principle of least privilege\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh [namespace]\n\n# Test for no wildcard permissions\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh [namespace]\n\n# Test ServiceAccount token automount configuration\n./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh [namespace]\n```\n\n### Run All Tests\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n\n# Integration tests (requires deployed instance)\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh\n\n# Security tests\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\nNAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh\n```\n\n## Test Coverage\n\n### Unit Tests (rbac_test.yaml)\n\nThe unit tests verify:\n\n- ✅ All RBAC resources are created when enabled\n- ✅ RBAC resources are skipped when disabled\n- ✅ Existing ServiceAccounts are used when configured\n- ✅ Custom RBAC rules are applied for controller-manager\n- ✅ Controller-manager Role has empty rules by default\n- ✅ Router Role has only secrets permission\n- ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD permissions\n- ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD status permissions\n- ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has core resource permissions\n- ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has pod status permissions\n- ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has event permissions\n- ✅ ServiceAccounts have correct labels\n- ✅ Roles and ClusterRoles have correct labels\n- ✅ ServiceAccount names follow naming convention\n- ✅ RoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n- ✅ ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n- ✅ ServiceAccount annotations are applied\n- ✅ Custom ServiceAccount name is used when specified\n- ✅ Resources are skipped when components are disabled\n- ✅ RoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n- ✅ ClusterRoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n- ✅ All RBAC resources use correct namespace\n- ✅ Custom namespace is used when specified\n- ✅ fullnameOverride is used in resource names\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nPermission Verification Tests:\n\n1. **test_workload_manager_permissions.sh**\n   - Verifies workload-manager can create pods\n   - Expected: yes\n\n2. **test_router_permissions.sh**\n   - Verifies router can list secrets\n   - Expected: yes\n\n3. **test_controller_manager_permissions.sh**\n   - Verifies controller-manager cannot delete pods (by default)\n   - Expected: no (if no custom rules)\n\nEnd-to-End Tests:\n\n4. **test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh**\n   - Deploys AgentCube with custom RBAC rules\n   - Verifies Role has custom configmaps rules\n   - Cleans up test deployment\n\n5. **test_existing_serviceaccount.sh**\n   - Creates an existing ServiceAccount\n   - Deploys chart using existing SA\n   - Verifies Router uses existing SA\n   - Cleans up test deployment\n\n### Security Tests\n\n1. **test_least_privilege.sh**\n   - Verifies each component cannot perform all operations\n   - Ensures principle of least privilege is followed\n\n2. **test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh**\n   - Checks for wildcard (*) verbs in all Roles\n   - Checks for wildcard (*) verbs in all ClusterRoles\n   - Flags any wildcard permissions for review\n\n3. **test_token_automount.sh**\n   - Checks automountServiceAccountToken setting on all deployments\n   - Reports current state for security review\n\n## RBAC Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Resource Scope | ServiceAccount | Role/ClusterRole | Permissions |\n|-----------|---------------|----------------|------------------|-------------|\n| controller-manager | Namespace | `agentcube` | Role | Custom rules (empty by default) |\n| workload-manager | Cluster | `agentcube-workload-manager` | ClusterRole | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n| router | Namespace | `agentcube-router` | Role | Secrets (get, list, watch) |\n\n### ClusterRole Rules (workload-manager)\n\nThe workload-manager ClusterRole includes:\n\n1. **CRD resources** (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n   - agentruntimes, codeinterpreters: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n   - agentruntimes/status, codeinterpreters/status: get, update, patch\n\n2. **Core resources** (\"\")\n   - pods, services, configmaps, secrets: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n   - pods/status: get\n   - events: create, patch\n\n### Role Rules (router)\n\nThe router Role includes:\n\n- secrets: get, list, watch\n\n### Role Rules (controller-manager)\n\nThe controller-manager Role includes:\n\n- Custom rules via `controllerManager.rbac.rules` (empty by default)\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Enable/Disable RBAC\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    create: true  # Set to false to disable\n\nworkloadManager:\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n\nrouter:\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n```\n\n### Use Existing ServiceAccount\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: false\n    name: existing-sa\n\nworkloadManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: false\n    name: existing-wm-sa\n\nrouter:\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: false\n    name: existing-router-sa\n```\n\n### Custom RBAC Rules\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    rules:\n      - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n        resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n        verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n      - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n        resources: [\"pods\"]\n        verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n```\n\n### Custom ServiceAccount Annotations\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    annotations:\n      eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n      custom.annotation: custom-value\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Permission Denied Errors\n\nIf you see 403 Forbidden errors:\n\n1. Verify ServiceAccount is bound to correct Role/ClusterRole:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings -n agentcube\n   ```\n\n2. Verify Role/ClusterRole has required rules:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl get roles,clusterroles -o yaml\n   ```\n\n3. Verify ClusterRoleBinding references correct namespace:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl get clusterrolebinding agentcube-workload-manager -o yaml\n   ```\n\n### Test Failures\n\n**Unit test failures:**\n- Check Helm template syntax: `helm template agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube`\n- Verify values.yaml configuration\n- Check for duplicate resource names\n\n**Integration test failures:**\n- Ensure kubectl is configured correctly: `kubectl cluster-info`\n- Verify AgentCube is deployed: `kubectl get deployments -n agentcube`\n- Check ServiceAccount exists: `kubectl get serviceaccounts -n agentcube`\n- Verify RBAC resources exist: `kubectl get roles,clusterroles -n agentcube`\n\n**Security test failures:**\n- Review wildcard permissions found\n- Check ServiceAccount annotations\n- Verify automountServiceAccountToken settings\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Principle of Least Privilege**: Grant only necessary permissions\n2. **No Wildcards**: Avoid wildcard `*` verbs unless absolutely necessary\n3. **Namespace Isolation**: Use namespace-scoped permissions where possible\n4. **Custom Rules**: Document reason for each custom permission\n5. **Regular Audits**: Review and audit RBAC configurations regularly\n6. **ServiceAccount Tokens**: Consider disabling automount when not needed\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes RBAC Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/)\n- [Helm Best Practices](https://helm.sh/docs/chart_best_practices/)\n- [AgentCube Design Document](../../design.md)\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen adding new RBAC permissions:\n\n1. Update the design document\n2. Add corresponding unit tests to `rbac_test.yaml`\n3. Add integration tests to verify permissions work correctly\n4. Update this README with new configuration options\n5. Run all tests to ensure no regressions\n\n## License\n\nApache 2.0","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:11] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [2:13] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"v1\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"kind\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [3:7] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"ServiceAccount\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpe