{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882549247,"sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad937cf0011kpNjyl0VKIm7M","messageID":"msg_d7ad8c6cd0016t656XryotNiDV","sessionID":"ses_28529fcb0ffesEh4piz4GFLCxM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-1f32796a4f094164a1e2a5fea18c99d1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`\n**Language:** YAML (Helm templates)\n**Status:** ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n\n#### Templates (Existing)\nAll RBAC templates were already implemented and follow the design specification:\n\n1. **ServiceAccount Templates**\n   - `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n   - `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n   - `templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n2. **RBAC Templates**\n   - `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n   - `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` (ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding)\n   - `templates/router/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n\n3. **Helper Templates**\n   - `templates/_helpers.tpl` (ServiceAccount name helpers)\n\n#### Configuration (Existing)\n- `values.yaml` - Complete RBAC configuration structure\n\n#### Tests (NEW - Created in this implementation)\n\n##### Unit Tests\n- `tests/rbac_test.yaml` - Comprehensive Helm template tests (24 test cases)\n\n##### Integration Tests\n- `tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify workload-manager can create pods\n- `tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh` - Verify router can list secrets\n- `tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify controller-manager cannot delete pods\n- `tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh` - Deploy with custom RBAC rules\n- `tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh` - Deploy with existing ServiceAccount\n\n##### Security Tests\n- `tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh` - Verify principle of least privilege\n- `tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh` - Check for wildcard permissions\n- `tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh` - Verify token automount configuration\n\n##### Documentation\n- `tests/README.md` - Comprehensive test documentation\n\n## RBAC Architecture\n\n### Component Permissions\n\n| Component | ServiceAccount | Role/ClusterRole | Scope | Permissions |\n|-----------|---------------|------------------|-------|-------------|\n| controller-manager | `agentcube` | Role | Namespace | Custom rules (empty by default) |\n| workload-manager | `agentcube-workload-manager` | ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n| router | `agentcube-router` | Role | Namespace | Secrets (get, list, watch) |\n\n### Workload Manager ClusterRole Rules\n\n```yaml\n# CRD resources\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# CRD status\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n# Core resources\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Pod status\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\"]\n\n# Events\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"events\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n```\n\n### Router Role Rules\n\n```yaml\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n```\n\n### Controller Manager Role Rules\n\n```yaml\n# Empty by default - custom rules can be added via values.yaml\n```\n\n## Configuration Options\n\n### Enable/Disable RBAC\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n\nworkloadManager:\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n\nrouter:\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n```\n\n### Custom ServiceAccount Names\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    name: custom-controller-sa\n\nworkloadManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    name: custom-workload-sa\n\nrouter:\n  serviceAccount:\n    name: custom-router-sa\n```\n\n### Use Existing ServiceAccounts\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: false\n    name: existing-sa\n```\n\n### Custom RBAC Rules\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    rules:\n      - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n        resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n        verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n```\n\n### ServiceAccount Annotations\n\n```yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  serviceAccount:\n    annotations:\n      eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n```\n\n## Testing\n\n### Unit Tests\n\nRun all unit tests:\n```bash\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n```\n\nRun specific test file:\n```bash\nhelm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -f tests/rbac_test.yaml\n```\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- ✅ All RBAC resources are created when enabled\n- ✅ RBAC resources are skipped when disabled\n- ✅ Existing ServiceAccounts are used when configured\n- ✅ Custom RBAC rules are applied correctly\n- ✅ Labels and annotations are applied correctly\n- ✅ Naming conventions are followed\n- ✅ Role/ClusterRole bindings reference correct ServiceAccounts\n- ✅ Namespace configuration works correctly\n- ✅ Component disable works correctly\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Permission verification\n./tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n./tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh agentcube\n./tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n\n# End-to-end tests\n./tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n./tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n```\n\n### Security Tests\n\n```bash\n./tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh agentcube\n./tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh agentcube\n./tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh agentcube\n```\n\n## Security Features\n\n### Principle of Least Privilege\n- Router has minimal permissions (secrets only)\n- Controller Manager has no default permissions\n- Workload Manager requires cluster-wide access but is bounded to specific resources\n\n### No Wildcard Permissions\n- All permissions use explicit verbs (no `*`)\n- Tests verify no wildcard permissions exist\n\n### ServiceAccount Security\n- Each component uses dedicated ServiceAccount\n- Names follow consistent naming convention\n- Token automount can be controlled via pod spec\n\n### Namespace Isolation\n- All namespace-scoped resources use correct namespace\n- Role bindings only authorize access within same namespace\n- Only workload-manager uses cluster-wide resources\n\n## Compliance with Design Document\n\nThe implementation fully complies with the design document:\n\n✅ **ServiceAccount Templates**\n- Controller-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n- Workload-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n- Router SA with correct labels and annotations\n\n✅ **Role Templates**\n- Controller-Manager Role with empty rules by default\n- Router Role with secrets-only permissions\n- Custom rules support via values.yaml\n\n✅ **ClusterRole Template**\n- Workload-Manager ClusterRole with all required permissions\n- CRD permissions (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n- Core resource permissions (pods, services, configmaps, secrets)\n- Status and event permissions\n\n✅ **RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding Templates**\n- Correct bindings between SAs and Roles/ClusterRoles\n- Proper namespace references\n- Correct roleRef configurations\n\n✅ **Helper Templates**\n- `agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName`\n- `agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName`\n- `agentcube.router.serviceAccountName`\n\n✅ **Values Configuration**\n- Complete RBAC configuration structure\n- ClusterRole rules defined\n- Component-specific RBAC settings\n\n✅ **Tests**\n- Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n- Integration tests (5 test scripts)\n- Security tests (3 test scripts)\n- Test documentation\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Status\n\n| Criteria | Status | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| ServiceAccount templates exist and follow naming convention | ✅ | All three components have SA templates |\n| Role templates exist with correct permissions | ✅ | Controller-manager and router roles |\n| ClusterRole template exists with all required permissions | ✅ | Workload-manager cluster role |\n| RoleBinding templates bind SAs to correct Roles | ✅ | All bindings correctly configured |\n| ClusterRoleBinding template binds SA to ClusterRole | ✅ | Workload-manager binding |\n| Helper templates generate correct SA names | ✅ | Three helper templates defined |\n| Values configuration supports all options | ✅ | Complete structure in values.yaml |\n| Unit tests cover all RBAC resources | ✅ | 24 test cases |\n| Integration tests verify permissions | ✅ | 5 integration test scripts |\n| Security tests verify best practices | ✅ | 3 security test scripts |\n| Documentation is complete | ✅ | Comprehensive test README |\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\nAs outlined in the design document:\n\n1. **Pod Security Policy Support** - Add PSP resources for enhanced pod security\n2. **NetworkPolicy RBAC** - Add network policies to restrict inter-component communication\n3. **Dynamic RBAC Management** - Support for dynamic RBAC rule updates\n4. **Audit Logging** - Add audit annotations to RBAC resources\n5. **Multi-Tenant Support** - Namespace-specific RBAC overrides\n6. **RBAC Testing Automation** - Automated permission testing in CI/CD\n7. **ServiceAccount Token Rotation** - Support for token rotation policies\n8. **External RBAC Integration** - OIDC-based service account authentication\n\n## References\n\n- [Design Document](../design.md)\n- [Helm Chart Documentation](./README.md)\n- [Test Documentation](./tests/README.md)\n- [Kubernetes RBAC Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/)\n\n## Conclusion\n\nAR-031 RBAC configuration is fully implemented and tested. All templates, configuration, and tests are in place and follow the design specification. The implementation provides:\n\n- ✅ Complete RBAC configuration for all three components\n- ✅ Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n- ✅ Integration tests for permission verification\n- ✅ Security tests for best practices\n- ✅ Complete documentation\n\nThe RBAC configuration is production-ready and follows Kubernetes security best practices.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:11] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [2:13] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"v1\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"kind\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [3:7] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"ServiceAccount\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"metadata\"\nERROR [4:9] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [5:3] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"name\"\nERROR [5:7] Unexpected map-val